**Expected behavior**
When the user is redirected to their Azure idp they can sign in. I expect that on successful authentication to the idp, the OnAuthorizationCodeReceived event is fired and I can step into that event. We do this successfully in our .Net Framework app to enrich the identity with some extra claim information etc.

**Actual behavior**
After the user has successfully authenticated through the idp, the events don't fore and they are returned to the login screen. Looking at the network traffic in the browser, a code and id_token are returned successfully. The one even that does fire is the OnRedirectToIdentityProvider event so I know the event wiring is working.

**Additional context / logs / screenshots / link to code**
The suggestion has been made to me that the authentication flow that I am experiencing is one that doesn't trigger these events and that I need to specify something else to make these events fire.
